{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"Plan-review PASS (signed, 0 blocking, 10 advisory + 4 overflow). Triage + design decisions:\n- [E2 f9e4b/ff3ab/fea34 field name + semantics] DECIDED: canonical field = applies_when, a list[str] of trigger TAGS (declarative data, JSON-serializable for project move files — NOT a callable). A move is APPLICABLE iff applies_when is absent/empty OR contains 'always' OR intersects the active_triggers set passed at selection time. 'triggers' in prose = the active_triggers argument; the registry FIELD is applies_when. Existing plan-review moves declare NO applies_when => always-applicable => no behavior change.\n- [E2 fafb1 selection semantics] DECIDED + ordered: (1) gate-on-surviving>0 (0 => no coach call, []); (2) deterministic applicability filter (applies_when vs active_triggers); (3) LLM picks among ONLY the applicable subset (move_id + bounded subject); (4) deterministic template render. A pick OUTSIDE the applicable set is dropped at render (render keys on the applicable registry), so the LLM can never select outside the applicable set.\n- [F1 f32626 'unchanged' baseline] DECIDED: compared to the pre-extraction rendered coaching — the existing offline workflow test (test_plan_review_workflow e2e) asserts the coaching for the always-applicable plan-review moves is byte-identical pre/post; a kernel test adds an applicability-filtered selection case (a move with applies_when excluded when its tag is absent).\n- [E1 feca9 / T4 f7901 old-code removal] ADDRESSED: a re-export-identity test asserts passes.render_coach_notes / _validate_subject / coach_instructions ARE the kernel objects (no second copy); MOVE_REGISTRY stays as plan-review's catalog INSTANCE.\n- [P6 f607d AC-quality / T7 f34d3 / T5e fea70 docs] DEFERRED docs to WS4 (epic seam+doc deliverable); WS3 adds kernel coach module docstrings recording the coach() contract + move-registry schema."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782609989508041001,"uuid":"cd4281ea-471b-4db8-9e81-aadbe98dda0d"}